    "chemicalDescription": [
      "sr-(Oligopeptide-184 Clostridium Botulinum Polypeptide-1) is a single chain recombinant peptide, produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene is synthesized by the fusion of the genes from Oligopeptide-184 and s-Clostridium Botulinum Polypeptide-1. The fusion peptide contains 476 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
